\subsection*{\codingRule{}}

A const-qualified object shall be initialized directly when declared.

\subsubsection*{Examples}

\noindent
\begin{minipage}[t]{\codelstwidth\linewidth}
    \lstinputlisting[
        xleftmargin = 3.4pt,
        firstline = 6,
        lastline = 12,
        title={Non-Compliant}
        ]{../code/coding-rules/rule-009/rule-009-non-compliant.c}
\end{minipage}
\hfill
\begin{minipage}[t]{\codelstwidth\linewidth}
    \lstinputlisting[
        xrightmargin = 3.4pt,
        firstline = 6,
        lastline = 14,
        title = {Compliant}
        ]{../code/coding-rules/rule-009/rule-009-compliant.c}
\end{minipage}

\subsubsection*{Reasoning}



